<br>
As far as scheduling epic raids goes.  The person who needs the piece from Plane XXX should schedule a time and date that is convenient to them, then thye should let an officer know this scheduled event and it will be added to the Guild MOTD.  Based on turnout, the raid will happen.  No one should complain if they didn't put up a reasonable schedule for their particular epic raid.  We can't help someone if they aren't online, or if they only have an hour or 2 to kill, or if they don't even let us know where they are in their epic.  <br>
<br>
As far as knowing who is where on their epic, the post we have floating around in the members section is about all we have for the moment.  Getting the support needed is not an obligation of the guild or it's officers, period.  Make friends with your guildies, and ask them to help out.  Your friends invite their friends, etc, etc, until you have what you need to make the raid happen. Simple as that.  As a raid leader I do not want to plan Hate Raids, Fear Raids, etc.  If no one else more qualified is present and I'm going along for the ride, I'll be more than happy to lead.  If I call a raid, it's going to be for something like ToV, Vindi, etc.<br>
<br>
As far as having people more qualified for leadership roles than others, that's a perception that I don't like people to get.  If you've been through a raid a few times and know basically what needs to be done, then you are qualified to lead as far as I'm concerned.  Everything else about leading raids gets picked up along the way.  The major limiting factor is yourself.  But yes, there are some people that get counted on to lead more raids than others. That is mainly based on their success in past raids, nothing more.  We are limited on those types types of people though, and I would like to see some more active leaders in our ranks.<br>
<br>
This is a social game, so I hope everyone is outgoing enough to say &quot;Hey, does anyone want to help with Mob_X?&quot;  I can not be responsible for people who don't take initiative.<br>
<br>
As far as getting the Epic Raid topic stickied, I'm not sure who's a moderator on these boards anymore besides Drydon.<br>
<br>
As far as stepping on toes goes, everyone here is an adult.  If you aren't this isn't really the guild for you.  I myself have no problem with being patient.  If you feel that because you scheduled a raid on top of someone else's that you are being slighted, you're selfish.  Help your guildie out, then ask them to help you out on yours.  It's all about friendships and nothing about stepping on toes.  You should be every bit as willing to help out your fellow guildmate if you ever expect them to do the same for you.<br>
<br>
Please don't get me wrong, as this post may sound rather harsh.  I'm just prone to giving people the raw facts, and it tends to rub some people wrong.  I'm really a nice guy once I get to know you, ask anyone (Well, almost anyone).  I just feel that new members should not be expecting to join Amazon to get their epics.  I'm way past wanting to farm epics and would rather be farming NToV at this point.  We've got a lot of newer people in the guild now, and I wish the best for you all as an Amazon, but that does not mean we're going to go out and farm epics for everyone.  <br>
<br>
We, as a guild, are capable of so much more if we concentrate on it.  The main thing holding us up now is the level range, put some levels on and our strength will grow tenfold.  Level 60 &gt; Epic for pretty much any class.  Very few epics have any lasting value in this game.  The only ones that make a big difference are epics with effects that are very expensive to come by elsewhere.  Examples are Swiftwind for rangers, Whistling Fists for monks, Water Sprinklers for clerics, Serpent Staffs for chanters.  Most other epic effects are worthless on a long enough timeline.  The saves on epics are nice, but based on experience, resists are nowhere near as important as levels when it actually comes to resisting.  A level 60 with 75 resists will always fare better than a level 51-55 with 200+, that's just the way it works. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/amazonguild/sigs/nuvarre.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
