<br>
In addition, I'd have to say that every calendar system is doomed to failure when it concerns mobs that are never up for very long.  Go to any major guild's webpage and look for their calendar, they don't have one for the most part, or it's been long abandoned due to it's uselessness.  The only thing they are handy for is all day farm-fest events really.  And even then it's not exactly foolproof because some other guild may have the same idea at the same time you do.<br>
<br>
Instead we, as a guild, should be more ready to organize on targets of opportunity that do pop up through the day.  In the past the major thing that has hurt us is the general lack of motivation when it comes to getting together for a target when it is called.  In my opinion, a lot of the problem lies in the general lack of zone connectivity knowledge.  At 55+ you should know how to get from the nexus to UP, or from CS to ToV. If you don't, there about 1,000,000 places you can go to find maps. And with the UI able to run in a window you have no excuse for getting lost anymore.  Hell, they've even added a map to the UI for most zones used for general travel.  Mobilization is key here, not planning.  <br>
<br>
When we do have a shot at something that drops good loot, we should have druids and wizzies doing pickups and people running as fast as they can to get to the nearest ring/spire.  With PoP and the PoK book system in general, almost every zone is within easy reach.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, Epics are a very personal stepping stone and I think everyone should get theirs.  But, I do not feel it is the responsibility of the guild to get each member their epic.  It is more the responsibility of the person, and the friends he makes along the way.  When I did my epic, about 1/4, maybe 1/2 of the people who came along to kill Faydedar were in Amazon.  I sat there and just asked friends to come over and sit with me throughout the day until I felt there were enough people present to make an attempt.  I ended up with major overkill and it was a very anticlimatic battle.  But, I am proud of it nonetheless <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/amazonguild/sigs/nuvarre.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
